- I see.

486
00:16:45,350 --> 00:16:46,860
They reached out to me that way too.

487
00:16:47,190 --> 00:16:48,819
- Through a DM?
- But what's important is...

488
00:16:48,820 --> 00:16:50,829
- that they don't cast you alone.
- That's right.

489
00:16:50,830 --> 00:16:54,029
- You go on the show with your ex.
- With your ex.

490
00:16:54,030 --> 00:16:55,360
- Yes. That's correct.
- Right.

491
00:16:55,730 --> 00:16:58,229
They ask you if you're interested in joining the show first.

492
00:16:58,230 --> 00:17:00,500
- The next step is a phone call.
- I see.

493
00:17:00,640 --> 00:17:02,070
They ask you about your dating history.

494
00:17:02,370 --> 00:17:05,640
And they pick the ex who they think...

495
00:17:05,810 --> 00:17:07,639
is the best fit for the show.

496
00:17:07,640 --> 00:17:09,709
- So among your ex-girlfriends, - That's right.

497
00:17:09,710 --> 00:17:11,879
they picked one to be on the show with you...

498
00:17:11,880 --> 00:17:13,019
- based on your love story?
- Correct.

499
00:17:13,020 --> 00:17:15,380
Did you call your ex to ask her to be on the show with you?

500
00:17:15,580 --> 00:17:17,549
No, the staff did that.

501
00:17:17,550 --> 00:17:20,789
A few of my ex-girlfriends had phone interviews...

502
00:17:20,790 --> 00:17:22,989
- with the staff.
- There were several of them?

503
00:17:22,990 --> 00:17:24,559
You're lying.

504
00:17:24,560 --> 00:17:25,690
He thinks it's a lie.

505
00:17:27,200 --> 00:17:30,469
Since I'm with these pretty boys,

506
00:17:30,470 --> 00:17:32,640
I look comparatively ugly.

507
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:35,840
But next to ordinary people, I don't look so bad.

508
00:17:36,610 --> 00:17:38,009
- I don't look so bad.
- Right.

509
00:17:38,010 --> 00:17:39,209
What's with you, Actor Jeong?

510
00:17:39,210 --> 00:17:40,839
- I'm not that bad.
- Be confident, Actor Jeong.

511
00:17:40,840 --> 00:17:43,349
- He's just like DinDin.
- I think the staff saw it in me.

512
00:17:43,350 --> 00:17:44,350
- Of course.
- I see.

513
00:17:44,351 --> 00:17:46,150
I'm sorry, but what do you actually do?

514
00:17:46,980 --> 00:17:49,620
- Why even act in a drama?
- What's with that tone?

515
00:17:50,590 --> 00:17:51,719
- You brat!
- Hold on a second.

516
00:17:51,720 --> 00:17:53,289
- Why are you being so aggressive?
- That's how he got onto this show.

517
00:17:53,290 --> 00:17:54,619
- I'm so curious about something.
- Okay.

518
00:17:54,620 --> 00:17:56,159
- Looking at you guys from here, - Yes.

519
00:17:56,160 --> 00:17:59,460
I can see two of you have very doubtful looks on your faces.

520
00:17:59,660 --> 00:18:03,100
I understand that Jang Hoon always has that look on his face.

521
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:06,240
- But Soo Geun keeps staring...
- Hey, I also...

522
00:18:06,540 --> 00:18:07,639
- We've worked together for years.
- What's the reason?

523
00:18:07,640 --> 00:18:08,739
Of course, he rubbed off on me.

524
00:18:08,740 --> 00:18:09,969
Anyone who is charming and good at acting...

525
00:18:09,970 --> 00:18:11,369
- can act in a web drama.
- That's right.

526
00:18:11,370 --> 00:18:13,610
- I'm curious about his old job.
- His old job?

527
00:18:13,710 --> 00:18:16,480
I used to be a video producer.

528
00:18:16,780 --> 00:18:18,579
- I used to produce videos.
- You worked in this industry.

529
00:18:18,580 --> 00:18:19,780
- You were a content creator.
- Correct.

530
00:18:20,220 --> 00:18:23,149
That's actually how I got cast in the drama.

531
00:18:23,150 --> 00:18:24,850
Since I used to work as a camera operator,

532
00:18:25,090 --> 00:18:27,660
I was well-acquainted with someone on the production team.

533
00:18:27,920 --> 00:18:30,329
That person asked if I was interested in acting in the drama.

534
00:18:30,330 --> 00:18:32,059
- That's how I got cast.
- Oh, I see.

535
00:18:32,060 --> 00:18:33,729
- So he was in production.
- I see.

536
00:18:33,730 --> 00:18:35,630
I shot my music video as well.

537
00:18:35,970 --> 00:18:37,169
- You did a great job.
- You're a pro at that.

538
00:18:37,170 --> 00:18:39,900
I shot it by myself, and the production cost was zero.

539
00:18:40,940 --> 00:18:42,940
- Next up is Su In.
- He's just like DinDin.

540
00:18:43,210 --> 00:18:45,509
We called him Seo Su In earlier,

541
00:18:45,510 --> 00:18:48,310
but his real nickname is Moon Booze In.

542
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:49,479
Moon Booze In?

543
00:18:49,480 --> 00:18:51,409
My friends call me...

544
00:18:51,410 --> 00:18:53,320
- by this nickname.
- Moon Booze In?

545
00:18:54,180 --> 00:18:55,419
I like drinking.

546
00:18:55,420 --> 00:18:56,550
That explains "Booze."

547
00:18:56,720 --> 00:18:58,590
I like drinking some beer...

548
00:18:58,890 --> 00:19:00,719
after exercising.

549
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:02,020
And I like hanging out with others.

550
00:19:02,630 --> 00:19:04,630
To be honest, recently,

551
00:19:04,760 --> 00:19:06,329
I played basketball with Jang Hoon as the coach.

552
00:19:06,330 --> 00:19:09,599
I did my best to earn deeper trust from Jang Hoon,

553
00:19:09,600 --> 00:19:11,270
but I often failed to perform as well as I hoped.

554
00:19:11,570 --> 00:19:14,240
- That's why I drank more recently.
- Because you were upset?

555
00:19:14,470 --> 00:19:15,569
- You... That's why...
- Because I was upset.

556
00:19:15,570 --> 00:19:18,169
(You... That's why...)

557
00:19:18,170 --> 00:19:22,240
- The reason...
- There's a misunderstanding.

558
00:19:22,810 --> 00:19:25,210
- Let me set the record straight.
- Clear the air, Captain Choi.

559
00:19:25,710 --> 00:19:28,519
Su In is normally very shy.

560
00:19:28,520 --> 00:19:30,949
But he likes drinking, and when he's drunk,

561
00:19:30,950 --> 00:19:32,690
Su In becomes adorable.

562
00:19:33,090 --> 00:19:35,720
After an upsetting match, Su In was the first to ask...

563
00:19:35,890 --> 00:19:37,660
if we wanted to grab drinks.

564
00:19:38,130 --> 00:19:42,229
But recently, I haven't heard him ask to go out for drinks.

565
00:19:42,230 --> 00:19:43,269
- Same here.
- Recently?

566
00:19:43,270 --> 00:19:45,470
- Yes. We had a match yesterday, - Yes?

567
00:19:45,670 --> 00:19:48,800
but Su In went straight home without asking us to go out for drinks.

568
00:19:49,340 --> 00:19:51,970
- It makes your body heavy.
- Charlie Charlie.

569
00:19:52,240 --> 00:19:54,380
- Charlie Charlie.
- Yes?

570
00:19:54,480 --> 00:19:56,080
- Charlie Charlie?
- Yes?

571
00:19:56,250 --> 00:19:59,480
Can Rising Eagles win the upcoming competition?

572
00:20:00,120 --> 00:20:01,549
- Let's see.
- No?

573
00:20:01,550 --> 00:20:02,949
He just said no.

574
00:20:02,950 --> 00:20:05,489
- No?
- Stop! Please say "yes!"

575
00:20:05,490 --> 00:20:07,520
- Yes.
- What?

576
00:20:07,560 --> 00:20:09,530
- No?
- No. Yes.

577
00:20:09,630 --> 00:20:11,690
- Will you lose?
- This is a delicate issue.

578
00:20:11,890 --> 00:20:14,499
- We'd better check out the show.
- By the way, Su In...

579
00:20:14,500 --> 00:20:17,699
had a nickname back in college.

580
00:20:17,700 --> 00:20:19,969
Apparently, it was Prize Hunter.

581
00:20:19,970 --> 00:20:20,999
- What was the prize?
- Prize?

582
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:22,469
That is his real nickname.

583
00:20:22,470 --> 00:20:24,140
What does Prize Hunter mean?

584
00:20:24,340 --> 00:20:25,969
Remember street basketball tournaments...

585
00:20:25,970 --> 00:20:27,339
back when you were little?

586
00:20:27,340 --> 00:20:28,839
- Yes.
- The 3-on-3 basketball.

587
00:20:28,840 --> 00:20:31,050
I loved taking part in those.

588
00:20:31,450 --> 00:20:34,579
I didn't participate with the prize in mind.

589
00:20:34,580 --> 00:20:38,520
Competing against the best players in the country gave me so much joy.

590
00:20:39,250 --> 00:20:40,989
- Winning against the strong.
- Like defeating all challengers?

591
00:20:40,990 --> 00:20:42,320
Yes, defeating all challengers.

592
00:20:42,890 --> 00:20:44,930
Winning a tournament...

593
00:20:44,990 --> 00:20:47,529
every week helped me...

594
00:20:47,530 --> 00:20:49,629
earn some pocket money.

595
00:20:49,630 --> 00:20:50,769
- How much?
- It was back in high school.

596
00:20:50,770 --> 00:20:52,030
How much was the prize?

597
00:20:52,430 --> 00:20:54,739
If I sum up all the prizes,

598
00:20:54,740 --> 00:20:56,240
it comes to around 40,000 dollars.

599
00:20:56,470 --> 00:20:57,540
The winning prize?

600
00:20:57,640 --> 00:20:59,169
But I competed for a good while.

601
00:20:59,170 --> 00:21:00,779
- Not from one?
- In total.

602
00:21:00,780 --> 00:21:02,509
- You really won the most.
- By the way,

603
00:21:02,510 --> 00:21:04,609
were the rules 3-on-3?

604
00:21:04,610 --> 00:21:06,079
- Yes, 3-on-3.
- So 3-on-3 games.

605
00:21:06,080 --> 00:21:09,220
In college, I played 5-on-5.

606
00:21:09,320 --> 00:21:12,219
I even won the President's Cup...

607
00:21:12,220 --> 00:21:15,290
at Kookmin University, where Kyu Min graduated.

608
00:21:15,590 --> 00:21:18,589
I also won the President's Cup at Yonsei University,

609
00:21:18,590 --> 00:21:19,659
- where Jang Hoon graduated.
- Really?

610
00:21:19,660 --> 00:21:22,399
Su In is above Jang Hoon.

611
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:23,499
Jang Hoon, you didn't win the President's Cup...

612
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:24,600
of your college, did you?

613
00:21:26,030 --> 00:21:28,239
- Goodness, he's amazing.
- Su In is amazing.

614
00:21:28,240 --> 00:21:30,109
- He's the best.
- You're the greatest.

615
00:21:30,110 --> 00:21:31,470
Yes, the greatest.

616
00:21:32,010 --> 00:21:33,809
You didn't win even one President's Cup, did you?

617
00:21:33,810 --> 00:21:34,909
- No, right?
- I'm afraid...

618
00:21:34,910 --> 00:21:36,009
I couldn't take part in it.

619
00:21:36,010 --> 00:21:37,279
I couldn't participate.

620
00:21:37,280 --> 00:21:39,679
- You should've trained your skills.
- Exactly.

621
00:21:39,680 --> 00:21:41,519
Didn't you participate in the National President's Cup?

622
00:21:41,520 --> 00:21:44,989
I wasn't qualified for Yonsei University's President's Cup.

623
00:21:44,990 --> 00:21:46,489
- Of course.
- You should've worked harder.

624
00:21:46,490 --> 00:21:47,759
- My bad.
- By the way,

625
00:21:47,760 --> 00:21:50,260
were you a basketball player, Su In?

626
00:21:50,430 --> 00:21:53,129
No. I'm just a street basketball player.

627
00:21:53,130 --> 00:21:56,170
I was in Bucheon back in high school.

628
00:21:56,370 --> 00:21:59,470
Jang Hoon was a player for the ETLAND team.

629
00:21:59,740 --> 00:22:03,240
His home court was right next to my high school.

630
00:22:03,610 --> 00:22:06,609
I went to watch their home game every day...

631
00:22:06,610 --> 00:22:08,979
and practiced Jang Hoon's basketball moves on the streets.

632
00:22:08,980 --> 00:22:10,250
What did you learn from watching him?

633
00:22:11,250 --> 00:22:13,720
His skills weren't something I could imitate.

634
00:22:14,080 --> 00:22:15,850
So I learned other things.

635
00:22:16,590 --> 00:22:18,650
- You know, like his footwork.
- I see.

636
00:22:18,750 --> 00:22:21,190
But his skills were something I couldn't imitate at all.

637
00:22:22,120 --> 00:22:25,030
That's why Su In has great footwork.

638
00:22:25,630 --> 00:22:27,729
You made the story sound natural despite simply memorizing it.

639
00:22:27,730 --> 00:22:28,760
Exactly.

640
00:22:30,130 --> 00:22:31,329
(Laughing)

641
00:22:31,330 --> 00:22:33,069
- He's happy.
- Of course.

642
00:22:33,070 --> 00:22:37,009
- He's loving it.
- Look at his big laugh.

643
00:22:37,010 --> 00:22:39,209
Su In, what's your actual job?

644
00:22:39,210 --> 00:22:40,640
They want to know his job.

645
00:22:40,840 --> 00:22:42,409
Many think I was a former basketball player,

646
00:22:42,410 --> 00:22:45,050
- but I made my debut as a model.
- I knew it.

647
00:22:45,280 --> 00:22:46,349
After enrolling the College of Physical Education...

648
00:22:46,350 --> 00:22:48,619
and getting discharged from the army,

649
00:22:48,620 --> 00:22:51,149
I was cast as a model and made my debut in a magazine.

650
00:22:51,150 --> 00:22:52,819
- A model.
- Then, I became an entertainer,

651
00:22:52,820 --> 00:22:54,820
and now I'm acting.

652
00:22:55,290 --> 00:22:57,989
Next is the team they're affiliated with.

653
00:22:57,990 --> 00:23:00,859
They belong to Rising Eagles.

654
00:23:00,860 --> 00:23:03,030
From what we heard from the last transfer students,

655
00:23:03,700 --> 00:23:04,729
it's a tough team.

656
00:23:04,730 --> 00:23:06,640
(If I do something I like...)

657
00:23:07,070 --> 00:23:09,170
(Seriously!)

658
00:23:10,240 --> 00:23:13,580
(Jang Hoon acts like a real boomer!)

659
00:23:13,710 --> 00:23:15,379
(Before I know it)

660
00:23:15,380 --> 00:23:17,210
(All tensed up)

661
00:23:17,450 --> 00:23:21,320
As a matter of fact, my wife is a friend with Coach Tae Sool's wife.

662
00:23:21,780 --> 00:23:23,290
They went to cheer at the game twice.

663
00:23:23,790 --> 00:23:25,949
I asked my wife to greet Jang Hoon...

664
00:23:25,950 --> 00:23:28,119
with a can of Dr. Pepper, his favorite drink.

665
00:23:28,120 --> 00:23:29,730
But she said things didn't look good.

666
00:23:30,160 --> 00:23:31,629
I made sure she didn't greet him.

667
00:23:31,630 --> 00:23:33,400
- Even back then?
- "Stay far away from him!"

668
00:23:33,830 --> 00:23:35,360
"I won't tell him you're there!"

669
00:23:35,760 --> 00:23:36,969
She went there three times to root for the team.

670
00:23:36,970 --> 00:23:38,170
So the mood was tense?

671
00:23:38,530 --> 00:23:39,640
How's the team atmosphere?

672
00:23:40,340 --> 00:23:41,369
- Is it okay?
- Charlie...

673
00:23:41,370 --> 00:23:42,670
- No.
- No?

674
00:23:44,010 --> 00:23:45,940
- Charlie Charlie is...
- Charlie Charlie.

675
00:23:46,070 --> 00:23:47,979
- Okay, got it.
- The whole team...

676
00:23:47,980 --> 00:23:49,239
is walking on eggshells around the coach.

677
00:23:49,240 --> 00:23:50,379
- Yes.
- Everything...

678
00:23:50,380 --> 00:23:51,509
depends on the coach's mood.

679
00:23:51,510 --> 00:23:53,219
- Yes.
- Yes?

680
00:23:53,220 --> 00:23:55,249
- Yes.
- He doesn't accept defeat.

681
00:23:55,250 --> 00:23:57,020
(Losing is out of the question for this man.)

682
00:23:57,050 --> 00:23:58,720
Really, we're the same,

683
00:23:58,850 --> 00:24:02,220
but he's giving it his all on that show.

684
00:24:02,930 --> 00:24:05,060
That's probably why he's much more immersed...

685
00:24:05,090 --> 00:24:08,460
and we get scolded every day.

686
00:24:08,630 --> 00:24:09,999
But his scolding...

687
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:12,570
is so that we'd improve.

688
00:24:12,670 --> 00:24:15,599
We tell each other not to take it personally,

689
00:24:15,600 --> 00:24:17,369
but as useful advice to help us improve.

690
00:24:17,370 --> 00:24:18,409
We already knew MINHO...

691
00:24:18,410 --> 00:24:19,639
- was good at soccer.
- Right.

692
00:24:19,640 --> 00:24:20,779
He's also good at all sports.

693
00:24:20,780 --> 00:24:21,809
- MINHO is good at everything.
- He's the ace.

694
00:24:21,810 --> 00:24:23,349
Were you also always good at basketball?

695
00:24:23,350 --> 00:24:25,379
Rather than being good at it,

696
00:24:25,380 --> 00:24:26,849
I've always liked playing basketball.

697
00:24:26,850 --> 00:24:29,619
But through this season, I realized...

698
00:24:29,620 --> 00:24:31,249
the basketball I knew...

699
00:24:31,250 --> 00:24:32,889
- was totally different...
- Of course.

700
00:24:32,890 --> 00:24:34,090
from the real thing.

701
00:24:34,290 --> 00:24:36,660
It's a completely different sport.

702
00:24:36,860 --> 00:24:39,930
It's so exhausting to the point I can't do anything else.

703
00:24:40,100 --> 00:24:42,059
I learned a lot through this season.

704
00:24:42,060 --> 00:24:44,029
Ever since I was young,

705
00:24:44,030 --> 00:24:46,670
I've always dreamed of becoming an athlete.

706
00:24:46,900 --> 00:24:50,069
The show made it feel as if I've become one,

707
00:24:50,070 --> 00:24:52,410
- which made me really happy.
- Nice.

708
00:24:52,610 --> 00:24:54,309
MINHO has been working really hard...

709
00:24:54,310 --> 00:24:56,780
- as the captain.
- Of course, because...

710
00:24:57,380 --> 00:24:59,979
- MINHO is a great runner.
- Exactly.

711
00:24:59,980 --> 00:25:02,679
He keeps running without getting tired.

712
00:25:02,680 --> 00:25:03,819
What about you, CHANYEOL?

713
00:25:03,820 --> 00:25:06,320
We know nothing about CHANYEOL's basketball.

714
00:25:06,860 --> 00:25:09,789
Honestly, I don't have any basketball background either.

715
00:25:09,790 --> 00:25:11,390
- Right?
- I started...

716
00:25:11,560 --> 00:25:14,559
playing basketball alone before joining the army.

717
00:25:14,560 --> 00:25:16,229
But you're the athletic type.

718
00:25:16,230 --> 00:25:19,100
I went out to the Han River and practiced shooting alone.

719
00:25:19,230 --> 00:25:20,499
- That was all I did.
- I see.

720
00:25:20,500 --> 00:25:22,139
Playing on a basketball team...

721
00:25:22,140 --> 00:25:24,510
like Rising Eagles was a first.

722
00:25:24,540 --> 00:25:25,740
Honestly,

723
00:25:26,010 --> 00:25:28,740
I still get nervous even when practicing.

724
00:25:29,180 --> 00:25:31,480
I'm not quite used to it yet.

725
00:25:32,050 --> 00:25:33,579
- That's why it's challenging.
- In 1, 2.

726
00:25:33,580 --> 00:25:36,389
I'm being completely honest when I say that...

727
00:25:36,390 --> 00:25:37,650
If CHANYEOL keeps practicing,

728
00:25:38,490 --> 00:25:40,319
he'll become a good player.

729
00:25:40,320 --> 00:25:42,360
- Of course.
- When it comes to basketball...

730
00:25:42,990 --> 00:25:45,129
Your basketball skills don't improve...

731
00:25:45,130 --> 00:25:47,129
if you practice only once every few days.

732
00:25:47,130 --> 00:25:49,329
For a second, it felt like advice from a senior comedian.

733
00:25:49,330 --> 00:25:50,899
- A speech.
- Yes, a speech.

734
00:25:50,900 --> 00:25:52,129
(Bull's-eye)

735
00:25:52,130 --> 00:25:54,399
You're about to dig in with the meat all cooked.

736
00:25:54,400 --> 00:25:56,410
That won't make anyone laugh, Shin Young.

737
00:25:56,540 --> 00:25:57,639
You're right.

738
00:25:57,640 --> 00:25:59,240
Why did you laugh on stage?

739
00:25:59,810 --> 00:26:01,209
- Just like that.
- I wouldn't bring this up...

740
00:26:01,210 --> 00:26:03,249
if you were impossible to improve.

741
00:26:03,250 --> 00:26:04,879
- Exactly.
- You can do it.

742
00:26:04,880 --> 00:26:07,479
- It's all because I care about you.
- Be persistent.

743
00:26:07,480 --> 00:26:08,649
Persistently.

744
00:26:08,650 --> 00:26:10,919
Kyu Min, how did you get into basketball?

745
00:26:10,920 --> 00:26:13,159
I started basketball...

746
00:26:13,160 --> 00:26:15,419
after reading the comic book "Slam Dunk."

747
00:26:15,420 --> 00:26:18,390
Tallness runs in my family.

748
00:26:18,430 --> 00:26:19,459
- What?
- What?

749
00:26:19,460 --> 00:26:21,200
- Really?
- Could we get some proof?

750
00:26:21,560 --> 00:26:22,799
(Asking for audiovisual proof)

751
00:26:22,800 --> 00:26:24,329
We're simply curious.

752
00:26:24,330 --> 00:26:25,330
You were born into a family...

753
00:26:25,330 --> 00:26:26,330
- of tall members?
- I'm serious.

754
00:26:26,500 --> 00:26:27,539
Give us an example.

755
00:26:27,540 --> 00:26:29,839
My grandfather has two brothers.

756
00:26:29,840 --> 00:26:31,739
They are 191cm, 185cm,

757
00:26:31,740 --> 00:26:33,439
- and 183cm tall.
- Your grandfather?

758
00:26:33,440 --> 00:26:35,809
My dad and my older brother are both over 180cm as well.

759
00:26:35,810 --> 00:26:38,150
- If all our relatives get together, - Yes?

760
00:26:38,610 --> 00:26:41,149
everyone is in the 180cm range. I'm the only 170-something.

761
00:26:41,150 --> 00:26:43,750
Your ancestors got all the height.

762
00:26:44,320 --> 00:26:45,890
- It seems like it.
- Is that so?

763
00:26:46,220 --> 00:26:48,159
After reading "Slam Dunk,"

764
00:26:48,160 --> 00:26:49,960
- I thought I'd grow tall...
- Of course.

765
00:26:50,060 --> 00:26:52,190
and imagined I'd either be Sakuragi Hanamichi or Rukawa Kaede.

766
00:26:52,430 --> 00:26:54,600
With that, I started playing basketball.

767
00:26:54,960 --> 00:26:56,030
But I turned out to be Ryota Miyagi.

768
00:26:57,830 --> 00:26:59,269
- And...
- What's wrong with Ryota Miyagi?

769
00:26:59,270 --> 00:27:01,399
- He's really cool.
- I like him.

770
00:27:01,400 --> 00:27:03,039
Didn't CHANYEOL...

771
00:27:03,040 --> 00:27:04,839
join in season two?

772
00:27:04,840 --> 00:27:06,169
Yes, I'm the only one who joined in season two.

773
00:27:06,170 --> 00:27:07,979
Did you accept the offer...

774
00:27:07,980 --> 00:27:09,580
to be on the show right away?

775
00:27:09,780 --> 00:27:11,849
To be completely honest, I was asked to join...

776
00:27:11,850 --> 00:27:13,679
- for season one.
- So you were asked.

777
00:27:13,680 --> 00:27:15,919
But it overlapped...

778
00:27:15,920 --> 00:27:18,389
with the solo concert that was already planned out.

779
00:27:18,390 --> 00:27:20,389
I was in no position to join the show,

780
00:27:20,390 --> 00:27:22,119
- You said no.
- which was a bummer.

781
00:27:22,120 --> 00:27:25,059
Much of season two overlapped...

782
00:27:25,060 --> 00:27:26,899
- with EXO's concert.
- Right.

783
00:27:26,900 --> 00:27:28,729
- I didn't think I'd be...
- I get it.

784
00:27:28,730 --> 00:27:31,470
of much help even if I joined the show.

785
00:27:31,500 --> 00:27:33,299
- I decided to turn it down.
- I see.

786
00:27:33,300 --> 00:27:35,039
- But when I went to the gym, - Yes?

787
00:27:35,040 --> 00:27:36,870
I met Jang Hoon by chance.

788
00:27:37,440 --> 00:27:39,910
He was in the middle of shooting "GYM JONG KOOK."

789
00:27:40,280 --> 00:27:43,010
Jang Hoon wanted to talk to me.

790
00:27:43,280 --> 00:27:44,910
- After talking to him, - Yes?

791
00:27:45,380 --> 00:27:48,450
I changed my mind, trying to fit everything into my schedule,

792
00:27:48,920 --> 00:27:50,149
and joined the show.

793
00:27:50,150 --> 00:27:51,319
- Personally cast.
- Personally cast.

794
00:27:51,320 --> 00:27:52,749
- Personally cast?
- That day,

795
00:27:52,750 --> 00:27:54,660
CHANYEOL walked into the gym...

796
00:27:55,020 --> 00:27:57,359
while we were shooting "GYM JONG KOOK."

797
00:27:57,360 --> 00:27:59,529
- I was like, "Perfect timing."
- "Perfect timing?"

798
00:27:59,530 --> 00:28:00,729
- "Perfect timing?"
- And so...

799
00:28:00,730 --> 00:28:02,060
- He dragged me into it.
- To where?

800
00:28:02,230 --> 00:28:03,470
The video.

801
00:28:04,470 --> 00:28:05,499
(Surprised)

802
00:28:05,500 --> 00:28:07,370
(CHANYEOL of EXO came at just the right moment.)

803
00:28:07,840 --> 00:28:09,239
Happy New Year.

804
00:28:09,240 --> 00:28:11,139
CHANYEOL. Perfect timing.

805
00:28:11,140 --> 00:28:12,740
- What is it?
- I had to talk to him.

806
00:28:13,410 --> 00:28:15,409
- There's a basketball show.
- Right.

807
00:28:15,410 --> 00:28:17,209
- I know that.
- "Passionate Basketball Team."

808
00:28:17,210 --> 00:28:19,179
I've got another tour with EXO.

809
00:28:19,180 --> 00:28:20,279
You don't have to be on every episode.

810
00:28:20,280 --> 00:28:21,619
Come whenever you can.

811
00:28:21,620 --> 00:28:22,679
We'll support you in every way possible.

812
00:28:22,680 --> 00:28:23,720
(Successfully cast CHANYEOL)

813
00:28:23,990 --> 00:28:25,819
You couldn't turn him down to his face, right?

814
00:28:25,820 --> 00:28:27,719
- Of course not. Yes.
- Yes.

815
00:28:27,720 --> 00:28:29,219
Charlie Charlie, yes?

816
00:28:29,220 --> 00:28:31,059
(A hard face to turn down)

817
00:28:31,060 --> 00:28:32,889
- Yes.
- I simply said...

818
00:28:32,890 --> 00:28:34,460
we'd support him whenever possible.

819
00:28:35,230 --> 00:28:38,629
Did things change within the team after CHANYEOL joined?

820
00:28:38,630 --> 00:28:41,739
When we have a game,

821
00:28:41,740 --> 00:28:43,210
- people come to watch it.
- Right.

822
00:28:43,340 --> 00:28:46,039
As the audience loves CHANYEOL,

823
00:28:46,040 --> 00:28:47,079
- Many fans must've come.
- They go wild.

824
00:28:47,080 --> 00:28:50,079
the volume of the cheers got much louder.

825
00:28:50,080 --> 00:28:51,109
(A noticeable increase in cheers)

826
00:28:51,110 --> 00:28:52,810
- What's more, - Yes?

827
00:28:52,910 --> 00:28:55,720
CHANYEOL is full of passion.

828
00:28:55,880 --> 00:28:57,950
- He runs with eager eyes.
- Right.

829
00:28:58,220 --> 00:29:00,120
There was a time I made a fast break.

830
00:29:00,220 --> 00:29:02,820
When I run, the defenders would normally surround me.

831
00:29:03,060 --> 00:29:05,430
But it was wide open, like an empty freeway.

832
00:29:05,560 --> 00:29:07,299
"Interesting. This is nice."

833
00:29:07,300 --> 00:29:09,000
"Great." With that, I made the shot.

834
00:29:09,530 --> 00:29:11,069
When I watched the game later on,

835
00:29:11,070 --> 00:29:14,040
CHANYEOL was running at full speed next to me.

836
00:29:14,200 --> 00:29:15,700
He drew the defense for me...

837
00:29:16,070 --> 00:29:17,109
- by running up first.
- He helped you out?

838
00:29:17,110 --> 00:29:19,109
The defenders must've wanted to be on the show more.

839
00:29:19,110 --> 00:29:20,439
- By standing next to me?
- Yes, being next to you.

840
00:29:20,440 --> 00:29:21,579
- I felt that a bit.
- Yes.

841
00:29:21,580 --> 00:29:22,639
That's it.

842
00:29:22,640 --> 00:29:24,009
"I have to be next to CHANYEOL, no matter what."

843
00:29:24,010 --> 00:29:25,249
"You won't be on camera over there."

844
00:29:25,250 --> 00:29:26,449
"Run to that side!"

845
00:29:26,450 --> 00:29:27,579
"It's CHANYEOL!"

846
00:29:27,580 --> 00:29:28,879
"We need to promote our team."

847
00:29:28,880 --> 00:29:31,649
"You won't be on screen if you stay on that side."

848
00:29:31,650 --> 00:29:33,359
- They want to be on screen?
- Anyway...

849
00:29:33,360 --> 00:29:35,590
I heard that Coach Seo had favorites...

850
00:29:35,920 --> 00:29:37,490
even when he personally recruited each player?

851
00:29:38,790 --> 00:29:39,859
- Really?
- He can't help it, though.

852
00:29:39,860 --> 00:29:41,929
You can't help but favor the better players.

853
00:29:41,930 --> 00:29:43,029
- Is that so?
- Sure.

854
00:29:43,030 --> 00:29:45,200
You also favored the good players on "Cool Kiz on the Block."

855
00:29:46,230 --> 00:29:47,299
- For those who were bad, - You were the same.

856
00:29:47,300 --> 00:29:48,599
you didn't even let them wear microphones.

857
00:29:48,600 --> 00:29:49,839
That's right.

858
00:29:49,840 --> 00:29:51,709
"Why are you wearing the microphone?"

859
00:29:51,710 --> 00:29:53,579
- He was like that on "Star King."
- "Do you have anything to say?"

860
00:29:53,580 --> 00:29:54,679
- You were like that.
- Sure.

861
00:29:54,680 --> 00:29:55,779
Back then...

862
00:29:55,780 --> 00:29:57,449
Back during "Star King," I had to stay backstage...

863
00:29:57,450 --> 00:29:59,410
- because I couldn't tumble.
- I'm sorry, but...

864
00:30:01,750 --> 00:30:05,119
(She mastered the tumble with sheer determination.)

865
00:30:05,120 --> 00:30:06,619
- I had to stay outside.
- For this,

866
00:30:06,620 --> 00:30:07,620
I won't argue back first,

867
00:30:07,621 --> 00:30:09,089
but I will hear it all, then argue.

868
00:30:09,090 --> 00:30:10,889
- After listening to it?
- Good.

869
00:30:10,890 --> 00:30:13,899
It's reasonable to have favorites...

870
00:30:13,900 --> 00:30:15,099
since the starting players...

871
00:30:15,100 --> 00:30:16,299
- are also more important.
- Right.

872
00:30:16,300 --> 00:30:18,329
- The coach shouldn't be like that.
- But...

873
00:30:18,330 --> 00:30:20,539
The most difficult part for Jang Hoon was that...

874
00:30:20,540 --> 00:30:22,399
he had to give everyone...

875
00:30:22,400 --> 00:30:24,139
- Sure. Since they have fans.
- fair playing time.

876
00:30:24,140 --> 00:30:26,879
He always shared that with us,

877
00:30:26,880 --> 00:30:28,379
and we knew about it.

878
00:30:28,380 --> 00:30:30,279
But one thing I wanted to say was,

879
00:30:30,280 --> 00:30:32,249
although we are playing basketball,

880
00:30:32,250 --> 00:30:34,119
- it's also a television show.
- Sure, it's a show.

881
00:30:34,120 --> 00:30:35,249
- Right.
- Of course.

882
00:30:35,250 --> 00:30:37,189
He called us over during the timeout,

883
00:30:37,190 --> 00:30:38,950
and he explained the game plan to us.

884
00:30:39,290 --> 00:30:40,789
The game had already resumed,

885
00:30:40,790 --> 00:30:41,959
and we needed to get back on court,

886
00:30:41,960 --> 00:30:44,259
but he kept going on with the tactics.

887
00:30:44,260 --> 00:30:46,289
Afterwards, before going back to the game,

888
00:30:46,290 --> 00:30:47,599
we were supposed to huddle up for the cheer.

889
00:30:47,600 --> 00:30:49,199
We were gathering together, but he screamed,

890
00:30:49,200 --> 00:30:51,369
"Don't do the cheer and just get back in the game!"

891
00:30:51,370 --> 00:30:52,370
(Banning the team cheer)

892
00:30:52,371 --> 00:30:55,199
- He did all the talking.
- The team needs a cheer.

893
00:30:55,200 --> 00:30:57,409
- You need to do that cheer.
- He's right, though.

894
00:30:57,410 --> 00:30:58,809
- If we don't hurry back in, - Yes.

895
00:30:58,810 --> 00:31:00,039
- we could get a penalty.
- Still.

896
00:31:00,040 --> 00:31:01,279
But he had already...

897
00:31:01,280 --> 00:31:03,309
- He had already...
- taken up some time.

898
00:31:03,310 --> 00:31:06,309
- We were already late, - You'd get the penalty anyway.

899
00:31:06,310 --> 00:31:07,949
We wanted to bring the mood up with our team cheer...

900
00:31:07,950 --> 00:31:08,979
- before going in.
- Yes.

901
00:31:08,980 --> 00:31:11,150
He said, "Don't do it and just get back in the game!"

902
00:31:12,390 --> 00:31:16,790
(Mr. Long Legs has his preferences when it comes to the team cheer.)

903
00:31:17,030 --> 00:31:19,259
- If I can add one last thing...
- Goodness.

904
00:31:19,260 --> 00:31:20,529
- I...
- How did you endure it?

905
00:31:20,530 --> 00:31:22,429
So, after that,

906
00:31:22,430 --> 00:31:24,200
since I was the captain, I told the members,

907
00:31:24,930 --> 00:31:27,299
"I will read his mood..."

908
00:31:27,300 --> 00:31:29,269
- For the cheer?
- "before doing the team cheer."

909
00:31:29,270 --> 00:31:30,539
(The era of team cheer suppression)

910
00:31:30,540 --> 00:31:32,309
- Why would you need to do that?
- So...

911
00:31:32,310 --> 00:31:34,079
- You need to read his mood?
- It's very important.

912
00:31:34,080 --> 00:31:35,709
- You need to read the coach's mood.
- Gosh.

913
00:31:35,710 --> 00:31:38,549
So I always read his mood before going for a cheer.

914
00:31:38,550 --> 00:31:40,379
He kept doing it even after that,

915
00:31:40,380 --> 00:31:41,580
and the problem is...

916
00:31:41,780 --> 00:31:43,279
I'll tell you the most important thing.

917
00:31:43,280 --> 00:31:45,620
I'll be honest, and you guys don't know about this.

918
00:31:45,750 --> 00:31:47,060
I've always disliked that.

919
00:31:47,490 --> 00:31:48,619
- Team cheers?
- Team cheers?

920
00:31:48,620 --> 00:31:49,890
Even when I was a player...

921
00:31:50,330 --> 00:31:51,389
- Just because you don't like it?
- Even when I was a player...

922
00:31:51,390 --> 00:31:53,659
- But the other players...
- It's for the team.

923
00:31:53,660 --> 00:31:55,529
- No. That's not it.
- The other players...

924
00:31:55,530 --> 00:31:57,700
We do that a lot in middle school and high school.

925
00:31:58,130 --> 00:31:59,730
In middle school and high school games, but...

926
00:32:00,140 --> 00:32:02,139
I think I didn't like it back then.

927
00:32:02,140 --> 00:32:03,200
Since we had to do it so many times.

928
00:32:03,670 --> 00:32:06,209
So after that, I don't do it.

929
00:32:06,210 --> 00:32:07,709
We didn't do it on the teams that I was on.

930
00:32:07,710 --> 00:32:09,379
- That's just for you.
- I know.

931
00:32:09,380 --> 00:32:11,479
- You can skip it.
- They wanted to do it.

932
00:32:11,480 --> 00:32:13,249
- They wanted to do it.
- But the coach...

933
00:32:13,250 --> 00:32:14,619
- Then...
- Hey.

934
00:32:14,620 --> 00:32:16,419
- Were there any teams...
- They did it.

935
00:32:16,420 --> 00:32:18,289
They did it. They all just did it.

936
00:32:18,290 --> 00:32:20,389
No, but they had to be cautious about it.

937
00:32:20,390 --> 00:32:22,219
- But...
- It was just once...

938
00:32:22,220 --> 00:32:24,059
- Why, you...
- They had to be cautious, and...

939
00:32:24,060 --> 00:32:25,929
Wait. Do you know what Jang Hoon said to me?

940
00:32:25,930 --> 00:32:26,930
What did he say?

941
00:32:26,931 --> 00:32:28,629
Would you have said it like that...

942
00:32:28,630 --> 00:32:29,800
- if it had been Lee Hyo Ri?
- What did he say?

943
00:32:30,100 --> 00:32:32,029
I said, "They had to be cautious about it," and he said,

944
00:32:32,030 --> 00:32:33,030
"Why, you..."

945
00:32:33,500 --> 00:32:35,040
- Come on.
- "Why, you..."

946
00:32:36,500 --> 00:32:38,609
- Come on.
- It's unfair.

947
00:32:38,610 --> 00:32:40,039
- Come on.
- It's okay.

948
00:32:40,040 --> 00:32:43,309
This isn't the co-ed experience I signed up for.

949
00:32:43,310 --> 00:32:44,310
- Gosh.
- No way.

950
00:32:44,311 --> 00:32:46,949
- Come on.
- He was like...

951
00:32:46,950 --> 00:32:47,950
"Why, you?"

952
00:32:47,951 --> 00:32:49,079
- It's okay.
- "Why, you?"

953
00:32:49,080 --> 00:32:50,819
- If you are happy...
- Gosh.

954
00:32:50,820 --> 00:32:52,419
- by saying it like that, - He said that.

955
00:32:52,420 --> 00:32:53,859
- then go ahead.
- What?

956
00:32:53,860 --> 00:32:56,119
How can I be happy when you said, "Why, you?"

957
00:32:56,120 --> 00:32:57,889
- I heard that from you.
- If you are happy to say that,

958
00:32:57,890 --> 00:32:59,329
then go ahead.

959
00:32:59,330 --> 00:33:00,330
- "Why, you..."
- "Why, you..."

960
00:33:00,331 --> 00:33:02,329
- "Why, you..."
- "Why, you are my friend."

961
00:33:02,330 --> 00:33:03,499
- I'm sure that's what he meant.
- "Why, you..."

962
00:33:03,500 --> 00:33:06,329
Since we're at it, do you have any complaints, CHANYEOL?

963
00:33:06,330 --> 00:33:09,699
To be honest, I didn't play enough games...

964
00:33:09,700 --> 00:33:11,540
to have any complaints.

965
00:33:12,210 --> 00:33:13,609
- Is that so?
- He really is the Cheering Fairy.

966
00:33:13,610 --> 00:33:15,809
- It was kind of unavoidable...
- Yes.

967
00:33:15,810 --> 00:33:17,949
because I missed a lot of games...

968
00:33:17,950 --> 00:33:20,079
- due to my schedule.
- Sure.

969
00:33:20,080 --> 00:33:21,849
And to be honest,

970
00:33:21,850 --> 00:33:23,079
I still have a limited understanding...

971
00:33:23,080 --> 00:33:24,289
- of the game rules.
- Right.

972
00:33:24,290 --> 00:33:25,389
- Sure.
- So...

973
00:33:25,390 --> 00:33:26,989
He has accepted it.

974
00:33:26,990 --> 00:33:28,159
So I did more cheering...

975
00:33:28,160 --> 00:33:29,389
- to bring up the team's spirits.
- Right.

976
00:33:29,390 --> 00:33:31,959
So I had less of a chance...

977
00:33:31,960 --> 00:33:33,259
- of getting in trouble, - You don't have a chance?

978
00:33:33,260 --> 00:33:34,759
and didn't have much to complain about.

979
00:33:34,760 --> 00:33:37,069
CHANYEOL is having the easiest time when it comes to that show.

980
00:33:37,070 --> 00:33:39,529
- That's right. Yes.
- "Yes."

981
00:33:39,530 --> 00:33:42,239
- Charlie Charlie. "Yes."
- "Yes."

982
00:33:42,240 --> 00:33:45,169
- For me, I always liked Jang Hoon, - Yes.

983
00:33:45,170 --> 00:33:47,079
so I always followed his directions.

984
00:33:47,080 --> 00:33:48,879
But once, I got in trouble...

985
00:33:48,880 --> 00:33:50,879
- even when I did as I was told.
- What? Why was that?

986
00:33:50,880 --> 00:33:52,180
Did he make you do a dunk?

987
00:33:53,310 --> 00:33:54,649
- That must be it.
- Yes.

988
00:33:54,650 --> 00:33:56,890
You should have told him that you can't!

989
00:33:57,990 --> 00:34:00,159
- You can't do everything.
- He was told to do it,

990
00:34:00,160 --> 00:34:01,390
- so he just made the action.
- Yes.

991
00:34:02,660 --> 00:34:05,289
Jang Hoon gives us lots of demonstrations.

992
00:34:05,290 --> 00:34:06,859
- "When you are playing defense,"
- Yes.

993
00:34:06,860 --> 00:34:08,059
- "reach out like this."
- Yes.

994
00:34:08,060 --> 00:34:09,299
"Block the shot."

995
00:34:09,300 --> 00:34:11,299
"I will throw a shot, so try and block it."

996
00:34:11,300 --> 00:34:14,039
So, he took the ball and stood like this.

997
00:34:14,040 --> 00:34:15,799
- He told me to reach out.
- You reached out.

998
00:34:15,800 --> 00:34:17,369
- He told me to try it, so I said, - Yes.

999
00:34:17,370 --> 00:34:19,139
"Okay," and went like this.

1000
00:34:19,140 --> 00:34:21,209
He looked down at me like this and screamed,

1001
00:34:21,210 --> 00:34:24,279
- "What are you doing?"
- Gosh,

1002
00:34:24,280 --> 00:34:25,349
that definitely hurts your pride.

1003
00:34:25,350 --> 00:34:26,549
- You just did as you were told.
- Exactly.

1004
00:34:26,550 --> 00:34:28,579
- Yes.
- You just did as you were told.

1005
00:34:28,580 --> 00:34:30,549
- Even if I reach up, - His hand...

1006
00:34:30,550 --> 00:34:32,649
I can't even shave his beard.

1007
00:34:32,650 --> 00:34:33,959
- You're right.
- Yes.

1008
00:34:33,960 --> 00:34:35,659
I told him to reach up.

1009
00:34:35,660 --> 00:34:37,059
- He did reach up.
- He reached up.

1010
00:34:37,060 --> 00:34:38,759
- Did he?
- I can't even reach his chest.

1011
00:34:38,760 --> 00:34:40,159
- He reached up.
- He reached up.

1012
00:34:40,160 --> 00:34:43,299
I think we need to listen to Su In's story.

1013
00:34:43,300 --> 00:34:44,899
You're loved so much...

1014
00:34:44,900 --> 00:34:47,539
that your nickname is "Seo Su In." But sometimes,

1015
00:34:47,540 --> 00:34:49,099
- it can be a burden.
- Yes.

1016
00:34:49,100 --> 00:34:50,509
The pressure is high.

1017
00:34:50,510 --> 00:34:51,869
- Right?
- Because of...

1018
00:34:51,870 --> 00:34:54,339
- the task I'm given.
- Yes.

1019
00:34:54,340 --> 00:34:55,839
I need to deliver,

1020
00:34:55,840 --> 00:34:57,909
- but it's not exactly easy, - Yes.

1021
00:34:57,910 --> 00:34:59,180
- so the pressure is really high.
- Yes.

1022
00:34:59,550 --> 00:35:02,779
And I'm the one who gets scolded the most.

1023
00:35:02,780 --> 00:35:04,490
The reason I scold him a lot is because...

1024
00:35:04,750 --> 00:35:07,889
Su In is currently a celebrity,

1025
00:35:07,890 --> 00:35:10,189
- and he is working as a model.
- Yes.

1026
00:35:10,190 --> 00:35:12,059
It's not easy for someone who wasn't...

1027
00:35:12,060 --> 00:35:13,959
a former athlete to be this good.

1028
00:35:13,960 --> 00:35:15,129
- Sure.
- To be honest.

1029
00:35:15,130 --> 00:35:18,329
So, he's a very special one.

1030
00:35:18,330 --> 00:35:19,729
But the problem is,

1031
00:35:19,730 --> 00:35:21,699
I have my expectations, so I keep scolding him more.

1032
00:35:21,700 --> 00:35:23,540
Am I favoring...

1033
00:35:24,170 --> 00:35:25,970
Do people favor others like this?

1034
00:35:26,410 --> 00:35:27,579
- No.
- No.

1035
00:35:27,580 --> 00:35:29,980
Su In really gets scolded the most.

1036
00:35:30,080 --> 00:35:31,080
(Hey! Moon Su In!)

1037
00:35:32,080 --> 00:35:33,209
(Moon Su In!)

1038
00:35:33,210 --> 00:35:34,820
(Number 5)

1039
00:35:35,280 --> 00:35:40,020
(Coach Seo is tough on Su In since he cares about him that much.)

1040
00:35:40,150 --> 00:35:41,389
He gets scolded so much that it's actually worrying.

1041
00:35:41,390 --> 00:35:42,919
- Really?
- You feel bad for him?

1042
00:35:42,920 --> 00:35:45,059
- I wonder if he's alright.
- Yes.

1043
00:35:45,060 --> 00:35:46,859
He comes right up to his face and says,

1044
00:35:46,860 --> 00:35:49,459
"I'm saying this to you one last time."

1045
00:35:49,460 --> 00:35:50,669
- That much?
- What?

1046
00:35:50,670 --> 00:35:51,799
To Su In?

1047
00:35:51,800 --> 00:35:53,739
- "One last time?"
- "One last time?"

1048
00:35:53,740 --> 00:35:56,600
"Take the ball properly and bring it up cleanly."

1049
00:35:57,140 --> 00:35:58,639
How hard do you think it must be? But he...

1050
00:35:58,640 --> 00:36:00,109
- Su In, it must be hard for you.
- I was worried,

1051
00:36:00,110 --> 00:36:02,179
so I told him, "You can do it. Don't worry."

1052
00:36:02,180 --> 00:36:04,009
- But he has a strong mentality.
- Yes, he's strong.

1053
00:36:04,010 --> 00:36:05,979
- He said that he can do it.
- Yes.

1054
00:36:05,980 --> 00:36:08,779
There's something that Jang Hoon says without even realizing it...

1055
00:36:08,780 --> 00:36:09,879
when he's mad.

1056
00:36:09,880 --> 00:36:11,819
"Oh, that's complete nonsense."

1057
00:36:11,820 --> 00:36:13,049
"That's ridiculous."

1058
00:36:13,050 --> 00:36:14,119
- He says that.
- Is there anyone...

1059
00:36:14,120 --> 00:36:15,260
- who talked nonsense?
- What?

1060
00:36:16,160 --> 00:36:17,659
There's someone who did something worse.

1061
00:36:17,660 --> 00:36:18,829
- What?
- Is that so?

1062
00:36:18,830 --> 00:36:20,699
- There was something worse?
- Is that so?

1063
00:36:20,700 --> 00:36:21,700
It's not just that.

1064
00:36:21,701 --> 00:36:23,229
- It's "all complete nonsense."
- Yes.

1065
00:36:23,230 --> 00:36:25,669
- There are five of us on court.
- It's all of them.

1066
00:36:25,670 --> 00:36:27,299
- "All complete nonsense."
- Is that so?

1067
00:36:27,300 --> 00:36:28,499
- It's all of them.
- It's all of us.

1068
00:36:28,500 --> 00:36:30,369
- "All complete nonsense."
- I see.

1069
00:36:30,370 --> 00:36:31,809
- MINHO is the captain, right?
- Yes.

1070
00:36:31,810 --> 00:36:33,779
Then are you satisfied with the captain, guys?

1071
00:36:33,780 --> 00:36:35,239
It's not just because I'm close with him,

1072
00:36:35,240 --> 00:36:37,679
but I really think he's doing...

1073
00:36:37,680 --> 00:36:39,779
an outstanding job...

1074
00:36:39,780 --> 00:36:42,419
as the captain of this sports team.

1075
00:36:42,420 --> 00:36:43,579
I really rely on him a lot.

1076
00:36:43,580 --> 00:36:45,449
- Right.
- When you see other sports teams,

1077
00:36:45,450 --> 00:36:47,389
if the coach is too tough,

1078
00:36:47,390 --> 00:36:48,689
the captain is popular.

1079
00:36:48,690 --> 00:36:50,429
That's right. If the coach is tough,

1080
00:36:50,430 --> 00:36:51,759
the team members get along well.

1081
00:36:51,760 --> 00:36:53,259
- Yes.
- Oh.

1082
00:36:53,260 --> 00:36:54,730
- We really get along so well.
- Jang Hoon...

1083
00:36:55,760 --> 00:36:58,269
- Right, Charlie Charlie?
- So well.

1084
00:36:58,270 --> 00:37:00,129
- Is that true?
- We really get along well.

1085
00:37:00,130 --> 00:37:01,369
- Is it true?
- Yes.

1086
00:37:01,370 --> 00:37:02,769
- Is it the best?
- It looks like it.

1087
00:37:02,770 --> 00:37:04,069
- Yes.
- That's right.

1088
00:37:04,070 --> 00:37:05,239
- Are you practically family?
- Do you get along well?

1089
00:37:05,240 --> 00:37:06,439
- We're even more than family.
- Gosh.

1090
00:37:06,440 --> 00:37:07,909
- Even more than family?
- It's even more than that.

1091
00:37:07,910 --> 00:37:10,879
When you're playing, who is the hottest-tempered?

1092
00:37:10,880 --> 00:37:12,449
- The one who is highly competitive.
- Yes.

1093
00:37:12,450 --> 00:37:13,509
- There's 1 person.
- Just 1 person.

1094
00:37:13,510 --> 00:37:14,519
- The greatest 1.
- There is 1.

1095
00:37:14,520 --> 00:37:15,749
- Who?
- Seo Jang Hoon.

1096
00:37:15,750 --> 00:37:17,219
- The coach was the one?
- Even I can tell...

1097
00:37:17,220 --> 00:37:19,390
- The coach...
- Even I can tell that it's me.

1098
00:37:20,620 --> 00:37:22,959
- It was like...
- Was there ever a time when...

1099
00:37:22,960 --> 00:37:25,929
Coach Seo got in a fight with the referee?

1100
00:37:25,930 --> 00:37:27,600
- There was.
- There was.

1101
00:37:28,160 --> 00:37:30,699
- Wait, what's wrong?
- Say it confidently.

1102
00:37:30,700 --> 00:37:33,229
- Yes.
- "Yes."

1103
00:37:33,230 --> 00:37:34,539
- Really?
- All the time.

1104
00:37:34,540 --> 00:37:37,069
- Really?
- It wasn't aired yet,

1105
00:37:37,070 --> 00:37:40,039
- but to tell you the story...
- I'm so curious about that.

1106
00:37:40,040 --> 00:37:42,509
A lot of people showed up that day.

1107
00:37:42,510 --> 00:37:44,009
It was completely full...

1108
00:37:44,010 --> 00:37:46,749
- with nearly 3,000 fans attending.
- Yes.

1109
00:37:46,750 --> 00:37:48,679
We were on court, and there was an unfair call.

1110
00:37:48,680 --> 00:37:51,090
There was an unfair call with only a few seconds left.

1111
00:37:51,820 --> 00:37:53,249
- He's the coach, right?
- Yes.

1112
00:37:53,250 --> 00:37:55,089
- But he ran onto the court.
- Gosh.

1113
00:37:55,090 --> 00:37:56,819
- Goodness.
- He has to run in.

1114
00:37:56,820 --> 00:37:58,359
- He ran onto it, - And?

1115
00:37:58,360 --> 00:38:00,059
and no one was able to stop him.

1116
00:38:00,060 --> 00:38:02,199
- No one could stop him?
- He was so upset.

1117
00:38:02,200 --> 00:38:03,299
- He was going crazy.
- Gosh.

1118
00:38:03,300 --> 00:38:04,699
- He has to respect it.
- Gosh.

1119
00:38:04,700 --> 00:38:07,869
- We had to calm him down...
- Gosh.

1120
00:38:07,870 --> 00:38:09,899
- during that time.
- Let me tell you.

1121
00:38:09,900 --> 00:38:11,439
It was such an important game,

1122
00:38:11,440 --> 00:38:13,739
and it was such an important moment.

1123
00:38:13,740 --> 00:38:15,339
The ball went out after hitting the opponent's hand.

1124
00:38:15,340 --> 00:38:16,609
- Yes.
- It was obvious,

1125
00:38:16,610 --> 00:38:18,109
- The ball went out...
- and it was unfair for us.

1126
00:38:18,110 --> 00:38:19,110
after hitting the opponent's hand,

1127
00:38:19,111 --> 00:38:21,679
and if accepted it,

1128
00:38:21,680 --> 00:38:23,280
- the game would end.
- Yes.

1129
00:38:23,750 --> 00:38:25,490
But...

1130
00:38:25,890 --> 00:38:27,860
- Sure.
- if I didn't go crazy,

1131
00:38:28,860 --> 00:38:30,660
- the game would end.
- The game would be over.

1132
00:38:31,960 --> 00:38:33,859
Since you went in, you should have done...

1133
00:38:33,860 --> 00:38:36,330
the Pikki Pikki Dance in front of 3,000 people.

1134
00:38:36,460 --> 00:38:38,800
- Did you just return?
- You should have done that.

1135
00:38:38,870 --> 00:38:40,470
(Pikki)

1136
00:38:41,240 --> 00:38:43,669
Where's the fan service when it's a television show?

1137
00:38:43,670 --> 00:38:45,069
- Right, MINHO?
- Yes.

1138
00:38:45,070 --> 00:38:46,139
- You have a cheerleader.
- Gosh.

1139
00:38:46,140 --> 00:38:47,439
You even have a cheerleader.

1140
00:38:47,440 --> 00:38:50,649
That's how serious he is.

1141
00:38:50,650 --> 00:38:52,309
We get life advice...

1142
00:38:52,310 --> 00:38:54,780
during every game and every practice.

1143
00:38:55,820 --> 00:38:58,290
So I guess it wasn't a fun shoot?

1144
00:38:58,720 --> 00:39:01,059
- Yes.
- That's right.

1145
00:39:01,060 --> 00:39:03,990
That means it wasn't fun.

1146
00:39:04,490 --> 00:39:07,599
- But to be precise, - That's the truth.

1147
00:39:07,600 --> 00:39:09,600
we may not enjoy the shoot, but...

1148
00:39:09,900 --> 00:39:11,829
On the court...

1149
00:39:11,830 --> 00:39:13,069
- Of course.
- Honestly, I don't always...

1150
00:39:13,070 --> 00:39:14,299
- enjoy filming, - I get that.

1151
00:39:14,300 --> 00:39:16,439
but I enjoy walking off court...

1152
00:39:16,440 --> 00:39:18,570
- after giving it everything I had.
- Of course.

1153
00:39:18,740 --> 00:39:21,579
He's pushing us harder so we can have that.

1154
00:39:21,580 --> 00:39:23,209
He gave you a real sense of accomplishment.

1155
00:39:23,210 --> 00:39:24,809
There's something I don't get.

1156
00:39:24,810 --> 00:39:27,010
We played basketball here even for the first season of your show.

1157
00:39:27,180 --> 00:39:30,020
When we played basketball then,

1158
00:39:30,080 --> 00:39:32,989
Yeong Cheol showed us some unbelievable skills.

1159
00:39:32,990 --> 00:39:34,089
That's right.

1160
00:39:34,090 --> 00:39:36,060
(Basketball Ace Yeong Cheol starred at the time.)

1161
00:39:36,190 --> 00:39:37,560
- You're the ace.
- The ace.

1162
00:39:38,260 --> 00:39:40,829
So we said Yeong Cheol would be joining Season Two.

1163
00:39:40,830 --> 00:39:42,129
- He won.
- That's right.

1164
00:39:42,130 --> 00:39:43,759
Why didn't you go all out...

1165
00:39:43,760 --> 00:39:45,430
- to recruit Yeong Cheol?
- Why didn't you?

1166
00:39:45,570 --> 00:39:48,439
I had absolutely no intention of going all out to recruit him.

1167
00:39:48,440 --> 00:39:50,910
You could've had him as your interpreter.

1168
00:39:51,670 --> 00:39:53,169
- He's good at English.
- With English at least...

1169
00:39:53,170 --> 00:39:54,439
- Right.
- You could've let him do that.

1170
00:39:54,440 --> 00:39:56,879
He's the Cheering Fairy.

1171
00:39:56,880 --> 00:39:58,079
- I could have been...
- The interpreter!

1172
00:39:58,080 --> 00:39:59,680
- the Interpreting Fairy.
- I'm sorry,

1173
00:39:59,780 --> 00:40:01,149
but let me just give you a clear answer.

1174
00:40:01,150 --> 00:40:04,349
- You're too old.
- That's right.

1175
00:40:04,350 --> 00:40:06,990
- You're too old.
- That's too harsh.

1176
00:40:07,320 --> 00:40:09,019
To have someone who's the same age as the coach on court...

1177
00:40:09,020 --> 00:40:11,130
- Yeong Cheol...
- That's too...

1178
00:40:11,660 --> 00:40:14,499
That image of being old is going to stick with you.

1179
00:40:14,500 --> 00:40:15,729
You'll keep hearing that.

1180
00:40:15,730 --> 00:40:17,700
- That's right.
- "Yeong Cheol? He's too old."

1181
00:40:17,930 --> 00:40:19,369
That's...

1182
00:40:19,370 --> 00:40:21,199
What are you going to do about that image?

1183
00:40:21,200 --> 00:40:22,399
You have to prove yourself otherwise.

1184
00:40:22,400 --> 00:40:24,239
That's going to stick.

1185
00:40:24,240 --> 00:40:26,710
- Just tell me I'm ugly instead.
- No.

1186
00:40:27,240 --> 00:40:28,880
- "You're old."
- You're old.

1187
00:40:29,210 --> 00:40:32,109
We've reached the last item.

1188
00:40:32,110 --> 00:40:34,880
What is this? It's called Truth or Misconception.

1189
00:40:35,220 --> 00:40:38,450
I think it's time to clear up some misconceptions or issues...

1190
00:40:38,850 --> 00:40:40,520
about the transfer students.

1191
00:40:40,890 --> 00:40:42,120
As for MINHO,

1192
00:40:42,560 --> 00:40:45,260
it's "MINHO's mom refusing to watch his shows."

1193
00:40:45,790 --> 00:40:47,700
- Your mother doesn't...
- Why?

1194
00:40:47,830 --> 00:40:51,699
My mother monitors almost all my shows.

1195
00:40:51,700 --> 00:40:54,440
- That's right.
- She always comes to my concerts.

1196
00:40:54,740 --> 00:40:56,540
If the concert runs for 3 days, she comes all 3 days.

1197
00:40:56,770 --> 00:40:57,969
Does she watch all the variety shows you're in?

1198
00:40:57,970 --> 00:40:59,140
She watches them all.

1199
00:40:59,240 --> 00:41:02,539
However, on YouTube,

1200
00:41:02,540 --> 00:41:04,379
- I film a lot of athletic videos.
- Right.

1201
00:41:04,380 --> 00:41:07,149
(Triathlon)

1202
00:41:07,150 --> 00:41:09,420
(HYROX)

1203
00:41:09,550 --> 00:41:13,450
(Athlete-YouTube-level content)

1204
00:41:13,790 --> 00:41:16,490
She tries not to watch the ones where I exercise.

1205
00:41:17,120 --> 00:41:20,359
- Why?
- My father was an athlete.

1206
00:41:20,360 --> 00:41:21,499
(Choi Yun Kyum, former soccer player and current coach of Yongin FC)

1207
00:41:21,500 --> 00:41:25,069
Ever since he was an athlete, and even now that he's a coach,

1208
00:41:25,070 --> 00:41:27,640
- she doesn't like the feeling...
- It must be tired.

1209
00:41:27,970 --> 00:41:29,970
of worrying about him.

1210
00:41:30,100 --> 00:41:32,540
But now, her son is also doing the same thing.

1211
00:41:32,640 --> 00:41:34,539
- She doesn't like...
- I understand.

1212
00:41:34,540 --> 00:41:36,240
the feeling of being anxious.

1213
00:41:36,410 --> 00:41:38,979
She's worried that she'll see you falling down or getting hurt.

1214
00:41:38,980 --> 00:41:41,079
She's worried she might see such things.

1215
00:41:41,080 --> 00:41:42,919
- She'd be anxious.
- So...

1216
00:41:42,920 --> 00:41:44,649
she tries not to watch them as much as possible.

1217
00:41:44,650 --> 00:41:47,420
But she still watches them in the end.

1218
00:41:47,590 --> 00:41:48,959
Do you still work out a lot these days?

1219
00:41:48,960 --> 00:41:50,320
What do you do?

1220
00:41:50,490 --> 00:41:51,559
- These days...
- I see you doing...

1221
00:41:51,560 --> 00:41:52,589
so many things on YouTube.

1222
00:41:52,590 --> 00:41:53,959
- These days...
- Triathlon. Didn't you do that?

1223
00:41:53,960 --> 00:41:56,699
Right. I started doing triathlons...

1224
00:41:56,700 --> 00:41:58,199
- last year.
- You started that.

1225
00:41:58,200 --> 00:42:00,569
There's a trending hybrid sport...

1226
00:42:00,570 --> 00:42:02,640
- called HYROX.
- What's HYROX?

1227
00:42:02,840 --> 00:42:05,869
- It's like an indoor...
- It's something really challenging.

1228
00:42:05,870 --> 00:42:06,870
fitness race.

1229
00:42:07,010 --> 00:42:09,610
It's a race where you run 1km and then do 8 different events.

1230
00:42:09,910 --> 00:42:13,950
- One kilometer?
- Many trainers do it these days.

1231
00:42:14,180 --> 00:42:16,779
I went to a competition and won first place.

1232
00:42:16,780 --> 00:42:17,920
You won first place?

1233
00:42:18,790 --> 00:42:23,390
(He won 1st place in 2 competitions!)

1234
00:42:23,460 --> 00:42:24,589
You won first place?

1235
00:42:24,590 --> 00:42:26,389
You won first place among all those trainers?

1236
00:42:26,390 --> 00:42:28,060
I went to the competitions, and...

1237
00:42:28,160 --> 00:42:30,500
- I also do a lot of running.
- That's right.

1238
00:42:30,700 --> 00:42:35,199
In my opinion, if MINHO had stuck with basketball...

1239
00:42:35,200 --> 00:42:37,200
instead of spending time on other sports,

1240
00:42:38,010 --> 00:42:39,709
That's something a coach would say.

1241
00:42:39,710 --> 00:42:41,880
If he had stuck with basketball,

1242
00:42:42,010 --> 00:42:43,539
- he could have made it big.
- Right.

1243
00:42:43,540 --> 00:42:45,910
I heard his running...

1244
00:42:46,180 --> 00:42:47,779
created some victims.

1245
00:42:47,780 --> 00:42:50,119
As far as I know, CHANYEOL is a victim.

1246
00:42:50,120 --> 00:42:52,249
- I'm a great victim. Yes.
- Yes?

1247
00:42:52,250 --> 00:42:53,349
Yes.

1248
00:42:53,350 --> 00:42:55,259
You're a running victim?

1249
00:42:55,260 --> 00:42:58,829
Last year, we held the SMTOWN concert...

1250
00:42:58,830 --> 00:43:01,100
- in London.
- Yes.

1251
00:43:01,360 --> 00:43:05,170
When we were there, I went to the gym with KAI.

1252
00:43:05,430 --> 00:43:07,299
I met Chang Min and MINHO...

1253
00:43:07,300 --> 00:43:09,969
- at the gym.
- You met the passionate people.

1254
00:43:09,970 --> 00:43:12,410
They were all ready to go running,

1255
00:43:12,910 --> 00:43:14,280
and they asked us to join.

1256
00:43:14,810 --> 00:43:17,409
(I'm on my way for a morning workout.)

1257
00:43:17,410 --> 00:43:19,209
(I was going to run with Chang Min,)

1258
00:43:19,210 --> 00:43:21,380
(but I think we'll have more people running with us.)

1259
00:43:21,480 --> 00:43:23,479
I went with them, thinking it was a light run.

1260
00:43:23,480 --> 00:43:25,150
- Right.
- I didn't even wear running shoes.

1261
00:43:25,250 --> 00:43:27,119
- So we ran five kilometers.
- What?

1262
00:43:27,120 --> 00:43:28,959
- We ran 5km.
- You ran 5km?

1263
00:43:28,960 --> 00:43:30,959
We even...

1264
00:43:30,960 --> 00:43:34,160
ran for more than 30 minutes.

1265
00:43:34,330 --> 00:43:35,459
It was really tough.

1266
00:43:35,460 --> 00:43:37,160
- My knees hurt so much.
- They hurt.

1267
00:43:37,330 --> 00:43:38,869
(I think I've got the runner's high.)

1268
00:43:38,870 --> 00:43:39,969
(Already?)

1269
00:43:39,970 --> 00:43:41,339
(We haven't even run 1km.)

1270
00:43:41,340 --> 00:43:43,699
(We've only run 800m now.)

1271
00:43:43,700 --> 00:43:45,269
(It's here. I've got the runner's high.)

1272
00:43:45,270 --> 00:43:48,380
(Already? How do you have it after just 10 seconds of running?)

1273
00:43:48,840 --> 00:43:52,309
After watching that clip, another YouTube team thought,

1274
00:43:52,310 --> 00:43:55,550
"It would be fun to make this guy go running."

1275
00:43:55,750 --> 00:43:58,620
So they cast me as the host of a running channel.

1276
00:43:59,590 --> 00:44:00,619
- Isn't that something good?
- That's good.

1277
00:44:00,620 --> 00:44:01,659
It's really good.

1278
00:44:01,660 --> 00:44:03,189
- Are you happy with that?
- Are you happy?

1279
00:44:03,190 --> 00:44:05,860
I'm really happy. It's really nice, but...

1280
00:44:06,330 --> 00:44:08,200
I perform at concerts,

1281
00:44:08,630 --> 00:44:10,559
- film "Passionate Basketball Team,"
- You play basketball.

1282
00:44:10,560 --> 00:44:11,699
- dance on weekends, - You dance.

1283
00:44:11,700 --> 00:44:12,829
- then I go running.
- You host the running channel.

1284
00:44:12,830 --> 00:44:14,069
The next day I play basketball,

1285
00:44:14,070 --> 00:44:16,670
- then I go running the day after.
- Your schedule...

1286
00:44:16,800 --> 00:44:18,770
- It's supposed to build my stamina.
- Yes.

1287
00:44:18,970 --> 00:44:20,210
But it's not.

1288
00:44:20,740 --> 00:44:22,410
It keeps draining me.

1289
00:44:23,010 --> 00:44:24,709
- You don't get to rest.
- Yes. So...

1290
00:44:24,710 --> 00:44:26,049
- It's too much.
- It's a little...

1291
00:44:26,050 --> 00:44:28,649
- Right.
- Actually, I didn't know.

1292
00:44:28,650 --> 00:44:32,319
I realized that I was pushing my standard on them.

1293
00:44:32,320 --> 00:44:33,489
I felt really sorry.

1294
00:44:33,490 --> 00:44:36,419
At the time, KAI...

1295
00:44:36,420 --> 00:44:38,060
had just started running.

1296
00:44:38,160 --> 00:44:40,859
- He had just started.
- So he said he loved running...

1297
00:44:40,860 --> 00:44:42,630
and went running around London...

1298
00:44:42,860 --> 00:44:44,429
on his own as well.

1299
00:44:44,430 --> 00:44:46,670
Then he quit running after that day we ran together.

1300
00:44:47,740 --> 00:44:49,099
We crushed...

1301
00:44:49,100 --> 00:44:50,500
- a promising young runner's dreams.
- It's tough.

1302
00:44:51,010 --> 00:44:52,870
- He said he wanted to die...
- He wanted to die...

1303
00:44:53,010 --> 00:44:54,109
while running that day.

1304
00:44:54,110 --> 00:44:55,880
(He retired from running after just one day.)

1305
00:44:56,710 --> 00:44:58,279
(It took less than five minutes to realize that was a big mistake.)

1306
00:44:58,280 --> 00:44:59,949
(After the run, I quietly wiped away tears in my hotel room.)

1307
00:44:59,950 --> 00:45:03,520
After MINHO's Truth or Misconception,

1308
00:45:03,650 --> 00:45:05,090
next we have Su In.

1309
00:45:05,320 --> 00:45:06,650
What's Su In's misconception?

1310
00:45:06,850 --> 00:45:08,560
It's "photobook trauma."

1311
00:45:09,790 --> 00:45:11,390
The trauma is coming back.

1312
00:45:12,490 --> 00:45:14,399
- Why is it coming back?
- When I was on "Handsome Tigers..."

1313
00:45:14,400 --> 00:45:16,330
with Jang Hoon before,

1314
00:45:16,700 --> 00:45:18,970
I gained a lot of fans.

1315
00:45:19,070 --> 00:45:21,869
To thank my fans for their support,

1316
00:45:21,870 --> 00:45:23,770
I released a photobook.

1317
00:45:24,570 --> 00:45:26,270
Since it was the first time making one,

1318
00:45:26,710 --> 00:45:28,479
I didn't know that it required a lot of money to make it.

1319
00:45:28,480 --> 00:45:29,979
The production cost kept going up...

1320
00:45:29,980 --> 00:45:31,480
- as I kept working on it.
- It would go up.

1321
00:45:31,710 --> 00:45:34,549
But since it was my first photobook,

1322
00:45:34,550 --> 00:45:35,649
I was ambitious.

1323
00:45:35,650 --> 00:45:38,820
I wanted to make it well. I wanted to do that for my fans.

1324
00:45:39,420 --> 00:45:41,859
So the production costs ended up being really high.

1325
00:45:41,860 --> 00:45:44,589
But then the sales were way lower.

1326
00:45:44,590 --> 00:45:45,859
Lower than expected.

1327
00:45:45,860 --> 00:45:48,199
So I took a big financial loss.

1328
00:45:48,200 --> 00:45:49,630
How many copies did you print?

1329
00:45:49,800 --> 00:45:50,930
Did you produce it yourself?

1330
00:45:51,530 --> 00:45:52,969
Yes. I produced it myself.

1331
00:45:52,970 --> 00:45:54,000
The editing...

1332
00:45:54,300 --> 00:45:56,239
- You did it yourself?
- I did it independently.

1333
00:45:56,240 --> 00:45:57,669
- Then...
- How many copies...

1334
00:45:57,670 --> 00:45:59,069
did you need to sell to break even?

1335
00:45:59,070 --> 00:46:02,779
If I sold 1,000 copies...

1336
00:46:02,780 --> 00:46:04,579
- A 1,000 copies.
- A 1,000 copies,

1337
00:46:04,580 --> 00:46:06,010
- That's...
- and you break even?

1338
00:46:06,350 --> 00:46:09,480
But only 300 copies were sold.

1339
00:46:09,720 --> 00:46:11,649
- Then...
- That explains the trauma.

1340
00:46:11,650 --> 00:46:13,189
- It would have hit you hard.
- So...

1341
00:46:13,190 --> 00:46:14,219
You could try making another one after this.

1342
00:46:14,220 --> 00:46:16,259
I didn't know he put his own money.

1343
00:46:16,260 --> 00:46:17,319
- Right.
- He used his own money.

1344
00:46:17,320 --> 00:46:19,165
Next. As for Kyu Min...

1345
00:46:19,860 --> 00:46:21,359
What's "Descendants of the Sun?"

1346
00:46:21,360 --> 00:46:23,130
- Are you talking about the drama?
- "Descendants of the Sun?"

1347
00:46:23,300 --> 00:46:24,769
- Yes.
- The drama...

1348
00:46:24,770 --> 00:46:26,500
I appeared in "Descendants of the Sun."

1349
00:46:26,770 --> 00:46:28,199
You also said you were on a web drama earlier.

1350
00:46:28,200 --> 00:46:30,600
- Which role did you play?
- You used to act before.

1351
00:46:30,700 --> 00:46:33,070
I was a soldier back then.

1352
00:46:33,270 --> 00:46:35,239
I served in the Special Forces.

1353
00:46:35,240 --> 00:46:37,880
- Really? Special Forces?
- They filmed at our base.

1354
00:46:38,350 --> 00:46:41,319
I appeared as an extra.

1355
00:46:41,320 --> 00:46:43,420
Like a cameo.

1356
00:46:43,620 --> 00:46:46,390
- Goodness, Special Forces?
- So,

1357
00:46:46,550 --> 00:46:48,159
Kyu Min was in the Special Forces,

1358
00:46:48,160 --> 00:46:49,659
- and MINHO...
- The Marines.

1359
00:46:49,660 --> 00:46:50,790
- was in the Marines.
- That's right.

1360
00:46:51,560 --> 00:46:53,359
Which is tougher, the Special Forces or the Marines?

1361
00:46:53,360 --> 00:46:54,929
That question isn't...

1362
00:46:54,930 --> 00:46:57,730
- I didn't go to the military.
- That's the wrong question.

1363
00:46:57,830 --> 00:47:00,969
From what I've heard... I wanted to hear about this.

1364
00:47:00,970 --> 00:47:02,300
In the Special Forces,

1365
00:47:02,500 --> 00:47:06,140
it's mostly the officers who go through the tough training...

1366
00:47:06,410 --> 00:47:08,909
while the soldiers don't do as much of it.

1367
00:47:08,910 --> 00:47:10,509
- Hey.
- So...

1368
00:47:10,510 --> 00:47:12,980
- Is it not true?
- I'm asking because I don't know.

1369
00:47:13,350 --> 00:47:17,149
I heard they don't do training, and they take care of regular duties.

1370
00:47:17,150 --> 00:47:20,150
- They take care of regular duties.
- I think you could explain that.

1371
00:47:20,420 --> 00:47:23,190
Of course, since it's a unit made up mostly of NCOs,

1372
00:47:23,360 --> 00:47:26,090
- we mainly handle support roles.
- Right.

1373
00:47:26,260 --> 00:47:29,860
But we still go through all the basic training as well.

1374
00:47:30,160 --> 00:47:31,700
Things like airborne training.

1375
00:47:32,030 --> 00:47:33,770
Jumping from helicopters...

1376
00:47:34,000 --> 00:47:35,899
at around 1,200m with a parachute...

1377
00:47:35,900 --> 00:47:37,669
We put our lives on the line to do those trainings.

1378
00:47:37,670 --> 00:47:38,809
You're talking about things you've done, right?

1379
00:47:38,810 --> 00:47:39,910
Of course.

1380
00:47:40,310 --> 00:47:43,080
We did parachute jumps about four times a year.

1381
00:47:43,440 --> 00:47:45,349
Since we put our lives on the line,

1382
00:47:45,350 --> 00:47:46,680
we even received hazard pay.

1383
00:47:46,980 --> 00:47:47,980
Do Marines also do parachute training?

1384
00:47:47,981 --> 00:47:49,619
- The Marines...
- I was also in an airborne unit,

1385
00:47:49,620 --> 00:47:52,349
so I jumped out of planes...

1386
00:47:52,350 --> 00:47:53,620
- with a parachute too.
- He...

1387
00:47:53,990 --> 00:47:55,289
He probably would've loved...

1388
00:47:55,290 --> 00:47:57,290
- jumping out of planes.
- Really?

1389
00:47:57,590 --> 00:47:59,059
That's exactly right.

1390
00:47:59,060 --> 00:48:01,359
- "This is also sports!"
- That's exactly right.

1391
00:48:01,360 --> 00:48:03,799
Your mother would worry about you.

1392
00:48:03,800 --> 00:48:06,770
Kyu Min, would you go back on "EXchange..."

1393
00:48:06,970 --> 00:48:08,069
or reenlist in the Special Forces?

1394
00:48:08,070 --> 00:48:09,200
What would you choose?

1395
00:48:10,300 --> 00:48:12,510
Would you reenlist and film "EXchange?"

1396
00:48:12,910 --> 00:48:14,170
- Tell us.
- What?

1397
00:48:14,780 --> 00:48:16,510
- Hold on.
- This is a tough decision.

1398
00:48:17,280 --> 00:48:19,109
I'll reenlist in the Special Forces.

1399
00:48:19,110 --> 00:48:20,379
(Going back on "EXchange" versus reenlisting in the Special Forces)

1400
00:48:20,380 --> 00:48:21,849
I really had a hard time in "EXchange."

1401
00:48:21,850 --> 00:48:22,979
- Mental stress...
- Really?

1402
00:48:22,980 --> 00:48:24,079
- is harder.
- It was really hard.

1403
00:48:24,080 --> 00:48:26,090
What about MINHO? Being a trainee again...

1404
00:48:26,250 --> 00:48:27,250
versus going back to the Marines.

1405
00:48:27,251 --> 00:48:28,320
For me, it's the Marines.

1406
00:48:29,020 --> 00:48:31,060
I really liked the Marines.

1407
00:48:31,230 --> 00:48:32,489
(Crazy eyes)

1408
00:48:32,490 --> 00:48:34,060
- You can work out all you want.
- Seriously...

1409
00:48:34,460 --> 00:48:36,029
Did you see how happy he was when we asked him that?

1410
00:48:36,030 --> 00:48:38,329
- His eyes...
- I think I helped bring...

1411
00:48:38,330 --> 00:48:40,970
a healthy and clean military service culture.

1412
00:48:41,670 --> 00:48:43,640
- Of course.
- That's a wholesome story.

1413
00:48:43,840 --> 00:48:46,609
The last Truth or Misconception is for CHANYEOL.

1414
00:48:46,610 --> 00:48:49,240
CHANYEOL wrote "visual scolding." What is this?

1415
00:48:49,840 --> 00:48:50,979
- "Visual scolding?"
- Does it mean you go around...

1416
00:48:50,980 --> 00:48:52,150
beating up people who are ugly?

1417
00:48:52,710 --> 00:48:53,909
- What is this?
- What's that?

1418
00:48:53,910 --> 00:48:55,449
- No.
- "Visual scolding?"

1419
00:48:55,450 --> 00:48:57,150
For the male idols,

1420
00:48:57,450 --> 00:48:58,820
there's a syndrome they get at least once.

1421
00:48:59,620 --> 00:49:00,949
It's the bulking syndrome.

1422
00:49:00,950 --> 00:49:01,989
It's a thing. It happens.

1423
00:49:01,990 --> 00:49:03,789
You go through it at least once.

1424
00:49:03,790 --> 00:49:05,760
- Right.
- When you debut,

1425
00:49:06,130 --> 00:49:08,099
you have a slender build.

1426
00:49:08,100 --> 00:49:09,999
But you want to achieve a masculine look.

1427
00:49:10,000 --> 00:49:11,299
- So you bulk up...
- Right.

1428
00:49:11,300 --> 00:49:13,029
- and build muscles.
- Exactly.

1429
00:49:13,030 --> 00:49:14,769
It happened to me once.

1430
00:49:14,770 --> 00:49:15,770
- You had it.
- Yes.

1431
00:49:15,870 --> 00:49:17,199
After I got discharged from the military,

1432
00:49:17,200 --> 00:49:20,009
- I wanted to look more masculine.
- I see.

1433
00:49:20,010 --> 00:49:21,610
I used to be very skinny.

1434
00:49:21,840 --> 00:49:23,539
But since I couldn't build muscle just by working out,

1435
00:49:23,540 --> 00:49:25,649
I ate a lot...

1436
00:49:25,650 --> 00:49:27,919
- to gain weight...
- Right. You should gain weight.

1437
00:49:27,920 --> 00:49:29,549
- and bulk up.
- You should get bigger.

1438
00:49:29,550 --> 00:49:32,849
But looking back now,

1439
00:49:32,850 --> 00:49:35,260
I realized the fans didn't really like it.

1440
00:49:35,520 --> 00:49:38,660
This is how I noticed that they didn't like it.

1441
00:49:38,960 --> 00:49:41,360
- I often monitor my performances.
- Yes.

1442
00:49:41,500 --> 00:49:43,830
It's actually easy to find videos of my performances.

1443
00:49:43,930 --> 00:49:45,969
But I couldn't find any videos from that specific period.

1444
00:49:45,970 --> 00:49:47,599
- Fans didn't post them.
- They didn't.

1445
00:49:47,600 --> 00:49:48,799
Fans didn't post videos from that time.

1446
00:49:48,800 --> 00:49:51,739
So, you just ruined your own looks.

1447
00:49:51,740 --> 00:49:53,239
So once I realized...

1448
00:49:53,240 --> 00:49:54,709
- they didn't like it, - Right.

1449
00:49:54,710 --> 00:49:56,740
I started to lean out again.

1450
00:49:57,340 --> 00:50:00,180
And two of the members...

1451
00:50:00,480 --> 00:50:02,080
- of EXO...
- Yes.

1452
00:50:02,220 --> 00:50:05,490
had the syndrome while serving in the military.

1453
00:50:05,820 --> 00:50:07,859
- They got it?
- They started gaining weight...

1454
00:50:07,860 --> 00:50:09,459
- and working out to bulk up.
- To bulk up.

1455
00:50:09,460 --> 00:50:11,990
So I told them to lose weight and lean out.

1456
00:50:12,290 --> 00:50:13,929
The video of me saying those things...

1457
00:50:13,930 --> 00:50:16,099
was posted online.

1458
00:50:16,100 --> 00:50:17,659
Can you tell us who they were?

1459
00:50:17,660 --> 00:50:18,829
They are SEHUN and KAI.

1460
00:50:18,830 --> 00:50:19,969
(Visual scolding members, KAI and SEHUN)

1461
00:50:19,970 --> 00:50:21,399
- He told us right away.
- But the thing is,

1462
00:50:21,400 --> 00:50:22,969
- They were so slim.
- you don't notice it.

1463
00:50:22,970 --> 00:50:25,669
I just looked in the mirror and thought I looked great.

1464
00:50:25,670 --> 00:50:27,539
- Right.
- So, CHANYEOL,

1465
00:50:27,540 --> 00:50:28,979
what kind of look do the fans actually prefer?

1466
00:50:28,980 --> 00:50:31,509
Basically, fans use terms like...

1467
00:50:31,510 --> 00:50:34,009
"leaning out" or "skinny as a thorn" to describe it.

1468
00:50:34,010 --> 00:50:35,979
- It means being bone-skinny.
- Bone-skinny.

1469
00:50:35,980 --> 00:50:36,980
